    <summary>A powerful shim manager for Windows that creates lightweight wrappers for executables</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
shimexe is a powerful shim manager for Windows that creates lightweight wrappers for executables. 
It allows you to manage and execute applications through configurable shims with support for:

- HTTP URL downloads with automatic executable detection
- Archive extraction (zip files) with multi-executable support
- Custom arguments and environment variables
- Working directory configuration
- Auto-update capabilities
- System PATH integration

## Features

- **HTTP URL Support**: Download executables directly from URLs
- **Archive Handling**: Automatic extraction of zip files with executable discovery
- **Flexible Configuration**: TOML-based configuration with extensive customization
- **Auto-update**: Keep your tools up-to-date automatically
- **Cross-platform**: Works on Windows, macOS, and Linux
- **Library Support**: Use as a Rust library in your own projects

## Quick Start

```bash
# Add a shim from HTTP URL
shimexe add mytool --path https://github.com/user/repo/releases/download/v1.0/tool.exe

# Add a shim from zip archive (auto-extracts and creates shims for all executables)
shimexe add plz --path https://github.com/release-plz/release-plz/releases/download/release-plz-v0.3.135/release-plz-x86_64-pc-windows-msvc.zip

# Run the shim
shimexe run mytool --help

# List all shims
shimexe list
```
]]></description>
